text:
Thanks for writing this up, it all sounds good to me! A few quick additions:

• To get to the correct number of features for the proposal we said we’d do a movie log where users can record star ratings for movies they’ve already watched. I also set this up to record the date they logged the movie. We should probably also display this on the profile page, maybe under the watchlist (hopefully we can reuse a lot of the code for displaying the watchlist to do this)
• Maybe in addition to ‘add to watchlist’, we can have a ‘log’ or ‘add to log’ button that displays when a logged in user is looking at a movie? We’ll probably also need a very simple interface to let the user rate the movie (currently set up to take a number out of 5 stars but this is easy to adjust)
• I think it would be nice if the ‘add to watchlist’/‘add to log’ changes to ‘remove from watchlist’/‘remove from log’ if the user has already saved that movie, and/or they see an icon (a star? an eye?) indicating that that movie appears on one of their lists, or the star rating they gave it, or something. Probably not the most essential thing at this point, but I think it would be a nice touch if we have time
How does this sound to people?

I like the idea of an eye for watched. Maybe log is just the code term and I misunderstood.

And for bullet 3. On click is actually fairly easy, I figured out how to send a post to logout on button click last night which is what I think your do to achieve that.

two things that popped into my head are:

1. Eventually display two ratings on movies— the one be from TMDB and the one from CouchCat users
2. Eventually add the ability for a user to exclude movies they have already watched from their results if they want

text: I like “rate and move to watched”! I think we initially said “favorites” but I think that’s confusing if it’s movie ratings since presumably people will sometimes be rating things they didn’t like, and I also thought about “watched” or “watched list” but that sounds too similar to “watchlist”. I think it could work for the button to say “rate and move to watched” and then the list displays as something like “watched movies,” “logged movies” or “rated movies”?
